@node "DISCLAMER" "Belive me, I'm not responisble"
@TOC main

                                 @{b}Disclamer@{ub}

 I can not be held responisable for any loss or problems you might recive
 by using this program.


                                   @{b}About@{ub}

                 Ultimate in WorkBench Startup Managmemt.

 This is a replacement for the much loved AutoStart 95.3 (I liked it anyway)
 and WBStartup+ v2.7. It manages your WBStartup drawer or at least what was
 meant to be in that drawer. This system is unique to any system of it type
 as far as I know. I say unique becaue it uses Drag 'n' Drop and the
 interface it almost totaly configrable, thanks to MUI.

 The two programs below are what gave me the idea.

 AutoStart 95.3 ©1995 to Ian J. Eimman
 WBStartup+ v2.7 © 1996 John Hughes

 @{i}AutoStart@{ui} was good because you could leave your programs where you want
 them. It also means you don't have to make copies off the programs you
 want to execute, which means you save space on you SYS: drive, you
 don't have duplicate copies of programs hanging around, and you have
 complete managiability of the programs you load.

 @{i}WBStartup+@{ui} is also a good program but not half as good as AutoStart is.
 The thing I liked about this program it the graphics that it had to offer.
 The managibility it gave you over the WorkBench start was not very good at
 all.

 Now by mixing these two programs together, adding some new ideas, MUI,
 Drag 'n' Drop and some tender loving care you get StartupPlus.
@endnode


