@node "FIRST" "A VIRGIN hay! Well soon change that :)"
@TOC USAGE
 @{b}First Time Users:@{ub}
 After installing StartupPlus you will find that there are a few more files
 lying around on your Hard Drive.  Now in the "WBStartup" drawer.  You will
 find this drawer on your SYS: drive.  There should be a program called
 StartupPlus.  Now click once on the Icon and use the WBench menu to edit
 the Icon's information or press LAmiga+i. They both do the same job.

 To load the data file you will need to place the DATAFILE ToolType into
 the icon. There should all ready be a template for it. If there is just
 click on it and edit away.

 e.g. DATAFILE=ENV:DataFile.sup3
 NB. SUP 1.6x uses the ext. '.sup3' if you try to pass any other extion you
 will get an error message.

 There are also some more @{b}Tool Types@{ub} in the Icon which can be set
 if you wish.  There not essicential and there is all ready a default set
 for the program.  see @{" Tool Types " link "TOOLTYPES" 0}
@endnode

@node "ASK" "The Ask Window"
@TOC USAGE
 @{b}Calling up the Ask Window@{ub}
 The Ask Windows general function is for you to play around with what you
 load on a Temp. basis only. You can also abort the program from here.

 There are three ways of doing this procedure.

 First their is the mouse. Just click on the main window with any of the
 mouse buttons. This will open the Ask Window.

 Secondly their is the Keyboard. By pressing the Left or Right Shift Keys
 at startup time this will open the Ask Window.


 @{b}Using the Ask Window@{ub}
 Project:
     Abort    LAmiga+a <--- Aborts the whole program
     -----------------
     About           ? <--- About StartupPlus and registration Details
     About MUI...      <--- About MUI and the version you are using
     -----------------
     Continue LAmiga+c <--- Continue with execution sequence

 Settings:
     Settings MUI...   <--- Call the MUI Prefs program


 There are two listviewers. The one on the left contains all programs with
 the Skip or Ask flags set. The other is contains nothing. Now by dragging
 one of the programs from the left listviewer over to the right listviever,
 the program will be added to the execution sequence.  When you press the
 @{b}'Continue with Execution Sequence'@{ub} button, anything that is now in that
 right listviewer will be executed.

 NB.  If you drag something over to the right listviewer that you know has
      the Ask Flag set, then drag it back again, that ask flag will be
      removed and replaced with a skip flag.  Any Drag 'n' Drop you make
      via the Ask window will not be saved.  So don't worry if you don't
      know what you are doing.  It will all come clear.
@endnode

@node "DISABLED" "Disabled? Well you soon will be!"
@TOC USAGE
 @{b}Disabling the program at Startup@{ub}

 @{b}LowLevel Method:@{ub}
 If you want to kill SUP before it loads hold down either of the Amiga keys.
 This will efficently disable it. If you are all ready in SUP hold down the
 ESC key. This will Terminate the program saftly.

 @{b}HighLevel Method:@{ub}
 If you have the Main window open and active (Making it active can only be
 acheved by clicking on the window. This will, open the Ask Window) you will
 be able to use The Left and Right Shift keys here as well.  The reason for
 not having the main window active is so that if you have a CLI/SHELL screen
 open it will not become deactiveated.
@endnode

@node "MORECHANGE" "Changing Files"
@TOC USAGE
 @{b}Changing the datafile at startup@{ub}
 By holding down the Left or Right Alt keys during startup, this calls up
 an ASL FileRequester. Just choose a diffrent file for loading and press
 the OK gadget. Normaly situated in the bottom left of the window.

 To set the Directory of where you keep your datafiles, edit the Icon with
 a line like this one:

 e.g. DATADIR=ENVARC:

 This will set the directory to use. If there is no directory set in the
 Icon, SUP will use the startup directory. In most cases this will be
 'SYS:WBStartup'.@endnode
@endnode

@node "CONVERTP" "Converting old datafiles"
@TOC USAGE
 @{b}Converting Old Datafiles@{ub}
 You can convert any StartupPlus data file just as long it has any of
 following extiontions. ".sup1 or .sup2"

 When you load the old datafile SUPPrefs will open a second requester
 asking for a file name. Give it any name you choose but remember to add
 the ext. ".sup3" if you do things wont work.

 Click on save and the old datafile will be loaded into the editor ready
 for anychanges you may which to preform on it.
@endnode

@node "LOADSAVE" "Loading and Saving"
TOC USAGE
 @{b}Loading/Saving DataFiles:@{ub}
 Loading a datafile is as easy as it gets unless you are trying to convert
 a file. If so see @{"Converting" link "CONVERTP" 0}

 Saving is just as you would expect. Give the file a name and it will be
 saved.

 Warning: The name of the file in the icon will be used for Loading
 and Saving. If you change the name of the data file you will need to
 change the name in both the icons.

 When saving make sure you end the file with '.sup3'. It's now essential!!!
@endnode

@node "ADDING" "Adding New Items"
@TOC USAGE
 @{b}Adding a program:@{ub}
 Drag and drop the icons you would like to run onto the ListViewer. This
 will add the program into your "Execution Sequence".

 If you have used SUP before this will confuse you. The @{b}New@{ub} button
 is now the string gadget. Just enter what you want to apper in the
 listviewer here and it will. Or you can use the gadget at the end of the
 listviewer to get the string info. Confusing at first.

 Any new item will be displayed with these settings:
          Execution Type: WorkBench
          Ask           : False
          Skip          : False

 If you changes these settings remember to save the file. If you forget to
 save them and try to quit you will get a notice asking if you want to
 save.

 NB: New items added will apper at the bottom of the ListViewer.
     The execution sequence of these programs depend on the order in
     which they apper in the executiion sequence.

 Also see: @{"Inserting" link "INSERTING" 0}, @{"Deleting" link "DELETING" 0}
@endnode

@node "INSERTING" Inserting new items"
@TOC USAGE
 @{b}Inserting a program:@{ub}
 To insert an item you will need to select the position in the list where
 you want it to be placed. Once you have selected and inserted an item you
 will have to change the content from @{b}»»» New Command «««@{ub} to
 something executable. To do this simply double click on the item and an
 editing window will open. Change/Choose a new command and click on
 @{b}Change@{ub} and it will be changed. 

 The editing of all commands is done in this way.

 Also see: @{"Adding" link "ADDING" 0}, @{"Deleting" link "DELETING" 0}
@endnode

@node "DELETING" Deleting items"
@TOC USAGE
 @{b}Deleting a program:@{ub}
 Delete's the currently selected item in the list viewer.

 Also see: @{"Adding" link "ADDING" 0}, @{"Inserting" link "INSERTING" 0}
@endnode

@node "EXETYPE" "Execution Types"
@TOC USAGE
 @{b}Changing the Execution Type:@{ub}
 There are three gadgets here: A cycle gadget, and two check buttons.
 Choose the execution type by choosing either:
          WorkBench     - Loads the program from its icon.
          AmigaDos      - Loads the program from the cli/shell
          AREXX         - Executes the AREXX script. You need Arexx running
                          before you can use this.
          Script        - Executes the DOS script
          Inline Script - Executes DOS scripts with out the need for a
                          script file.

 With an Inline Script you can put more than one command on a line in
 the editor. The example below are the first three lines of my
 StartupSequence. As you can see they are on the same line only
 seperated by a comma and a space (', ') if these arn't in the line it
 won't work.

 Example:
 C:MakeDir RAM:T RAM:Clipboards RAM:ENV RAM:ENV/Sys, Assign >NIL: ENV: RAM:ENV, C:Copy >NIL: ENVARC: RAM:ENV ALL NOREQ

 Look at the example datafile supplied with this archive.
@endnode

@node "ASKSKIP" "Ask and Skip Types"
@TOC USAGE
 @{b}Ask & Skip@{ub}
 Ask:  Ask's the user during startup if they want to execute the program
 Skip: Skips the prorgam all together when started.

 NB. You can only have one or the other.
@endnode

@node "ORDER" "Execution Order of Programs"
@TOC USAGE
 @{b}Execution Order:@{ub}
 The Execution order is the order that it appers in the Listviewer. It can
 be changed by using the Drag 'n' Drop sorting tequnique that is unique to
 this Startup Program as far as I know.
@endnode

@node "CHANGE" "Changing an Item"
@TOC USAGE
 @{b}Changing an Item in the List@{ub}
 To Edit an item double click on it and a editing window will appear. Enter
 the new command or use the @{b}Get@{ub} function at the end of the line.
 If you decide at any time that you don't want to make the changes just
 click on @{b}Abort@{ub} or the @{b}Window@{ub} Close button in the top left of the window.
 No changes will be made unless you click on @{b}Change@{ub}
@endnode

@node "EDITING" "Changing files from SUPPrefs"
@TOC USAGE
 @{b}@{u}Menu Item:@{ub}@{uu} @{i}Edit Icon/ARexx/Script@{ui}
 This is a multifunctional item that will let you via the editor change the
 content of files and Icons.

 To use this fuction select any command from the @{i}Execution Sequence@{ui}
 and invoke the function.
@endnode

@node "TESTING" "Test a new Item"
@TOC USAGE
 @{b}Testing to see if the item works@{ub}
 @{b}@{i}@{u}WARNING@{ub}@{ui}@{uu} Some programs will crash your system if run from WorkBench and
 others just won't work. Same applys for AmigaDOS!!! The fault lies with
 the programmer of the program you are trying to run and not with this one.

                           @{b}YOU HAVE BEEN WARNED@{ub}

 Select the item from the @{i}Execution Sequence@{ui} and invoke the Test
 function. If it works the program will load. If it doesn't it won't.
@endnode

@node "TOOLTYPESP" "Whats in the Icon..."
@TOC USAGE
 @{b}What bit does what@{ub}

 @{b}TOOLTYPES@{ub}
 DATAFILE/s     - The name and location of the datafile.

 TEXTEDITOR/s   - Enter the name of you choosen text editer here.
                  Default is @{b}ED@{ub}.

 HELPBUBBLES/b  - Boolean value (TRUE|FALSE) Default is TRUE

 HELPFILE/s     - Where the helpfile is located. Default is @{b}'Help:'@{ub}
                  This just gives you the power to decide where the
                  help file lives.

 FORTUNECOOKIES - Stops little helpful hints popping up. If you haven't
                  used SUP before they are kind of handy. Default is TRUE

 SUPLOCATION    - Location of SUP. Sounds silly but if you rename it
                  SUPPrefs needs to know.
                  
 SUPPLOCATION   - Same as SUPLOCATION but for the Prefs Program.
@endnode

@node "TOOLTYPES" "Whats in the Icon..."
@TOC USAGE
 @{b}What bit does what@{ub}

 @{b}TOOLTYPES@{ub}
 DATAFILE/s     - The name and location of the datafile.

 DATADIR/s      - Location of datafile storage.

 DISABLED/b     - Is SUP to disabled at startup? Default is FALSE

 ASKATSTARTUP/b - Open the Ask Window At Startup? Default is FALSE

 VOIDASK/b      - Force all ASK's to become SKIP's! Default id FALSE
 
 WINDOW/b       - Open the Window? Default is TRUE
@endnode

@node "ICON" "Changing SUP and SUPPrefs Icons"
@TOC USAGE
 @{b}Changing the content of The Main Icons@{ub}
 Use this function to edit the SUP and SUPPrefs icons. Saves you having to
 hunt round for them.
@endnode

@node "BACKGROUND" "Changing the background"
@TOC USAGE
 @{b}Changing the Background@{ub}
 Not an easy task but it is possible.
 · First open the @{b}MUI preferences@{ub} program. If you don't have it,
   why not!
 · You can either do this via the MUI program or via StartupPlus's 'Ask'
   Window under 'Settings/Settings MUI...'. You might also have a
   dropdown menu in the right hand corner of the window.
 · Now goto the menu and under @{i}Project@{ui} you will find an @{i}Open@{ui} Function.
   Use it.
 · Now you should have file requester. Press on the @{b}'Volumes'@{ub} button
   and then find and click on @{b}'EnvArc:'@{ub}. When the listviewer has finished
   displaying the @{i}'EnvArc:'@{ui} directory click on @{b}'MUI'@{ub} directory.
 · Click on @{b}'STARTUPPLUS.prefs'@{ub} and then on the @{b}'OK'@{ub} button.
 · If you haven't yet got a file called @{b}STARTUPPLUS.prefs@{ub} don't
   worry. Either run @{b}StartupPlus@{ub} or when you come to same the file
   then give it the name @{b}STARTUPPLUS.prefs@{ub}.
 · The preferences file should now be loaded in to MUI.
 · You might have noticed that there is no change in the way the MUI
   Prefrences looks.  Ok, so click on the test button to initial the
   changed preferences.  If there is still no physical diffrence don't
   worry.  You just can't see it yet.
 · Now click on the bit marked @{b}Windows@{ub} in the MUI Listviewer.
 · The window should change it apperance, with new gadgets and options.
 · In the top right hand corner of this window is an borded section named
   @{b}Background@{ub}.
 · Now you should be aware of two boxes, one named @{b}'Window'@{ub} and the other
   called @{b}'Requester'@{ub}.
 · Click on the box with @{b}'Window'@{ub} printed below it and a new smaller window
   will apper called @{b}'Abjust Background'@{ub}.
 · There are three pages to choose from. @{b}'Pattern' 'Color'@{ub} and @{b}'Bitmap'@{ub}

 @{b}@{i}Pattern:@{ub}@{ui}
        · Under 'Pattern' you have to choice of 18 diffrent patterns.
        · Choose a colour or pattern and click on @{b}'OK'@{ub}.
        1 Now the @{i}'Window'@{ui} should have changed to the pattern or colour
          you have just chosen.
        2 Now go back to the menu and choose @{b}'Save As'@{ub}.
        3 Now you should have file requester. Press on the @{b}'Volumes'@{ub}
          button and then click on @{b}'EnvArc:'@{ub}. When the listviewer has
          finished displaying the @{i}'EnvArc:'@{ui} dir click on @{b}'MUI'@{ub}
          directory.
        4 Click on @{b}'STARTUPPLUS.prefs'@{ub} and then on the @{b}'OK'@{ub}
          button.
        5 Do steps 2 to 4 again but this time you want @{b}'Env:'@{ub} and not
          @{b}'EnvArc:'@{ub}.
        6 When you have saved both of these files click on the @{b}'Cancel'@{ub}
          button. @{i}Do not click on the the @{b}Save@{ub} button. This will
          save you new preferences as a global preference for all MUI
          applications.@{ui}

 @{b}@{i}Color:@{ub}@{ui}
        · Under @{b}'Color'@{ub} there are three More pages.
          @{b}'MUI' 'Colormap'@{ub} and  @{b}'RGB'@{ub}
        1 Choose a page and colour and click on @{b}'OK'@{ub}.
        2 Now the @{i}'Window'@{ui} should have changed to the colour you have
          just chosen.
        3 Now go back to the menu and choose @{b}'Save As'@{ub}.
        4 Now you should have file requester. Press on the @{b}'Volumes'@{ub}
          button and then click on @{b}'EnvArc:'@{ub}. When the listviewer has
          finished displaying the @{i}'EnvArc:'@{ui} dir click on @{b}'MUI'@{ub}
          directory.
        5 Click on @{b}'STARTUPPLUS.1.prefs'@{ub} and then on the @{b}'OK'@{ub}
          button.
        6 Do steps 3 to 5 again but this time you want @{b}'Env:'@{ub} and not
          @{b}'EnvArc:'@{ub}.
        7 When you have saved both of these files click on the @{b}'Cancel'@{ub}
          button. @{i}Do not click on the the @{b}Save@{ub} button. This will
          save you new preferences as a global preference for all MUI
          applications.@{ui}

 @{b}@{i}Bitmap:@{ub}@{ui}
        · Either enter the path and name of the picture you want to display.
        · You can use the get button at the end of the string gadget to
          get the path and name of a picture.
        1 Now the @{i}'Window'@{ui} should have changed to the picture you have
          just chosen.
        2 Now go back to the menu and choose @{b}'Save As'@{ub}.
        3 Now you should have file requester. Press on the @{b}'Volumes'@{ub}
          button and then click on @{b}'EnvArc:'@{ub}. When the listviewer has
          finished displaying the @{i}'EnvArc:'@{ui} dir click on @{b}'MUI'@{ub}
          directory.
        4 Click on @{b}'STARTUPPLUS.prefs'@{ub} and then on the @{b}'OK'@{ub}
          button.
        5 Do steps 2 to 4 again but this time you want @{b}'Env:'@{ub} and not
          @{b}'EnvArc:'@{ub}.
        6 When you have saved both of these files click on the @{b}'Cancel'@{ub}
          button. @{i}Do not click on the the @{b}Save@{ub} button. This will
          save you new preferences as a global preference for all MUI
          applications.@{ui}
@endnode


